 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.307","title":"[audit][plan] Make ExtractionCertificate::verify reject tampered cost metadata","description":"src/plan/extractor.rs currently verifies only certificate version, plan hash, and node count. The extracted cost field can be tampered with and ExtractionCertificate::verify still returns Ok, which defeats the certificate's stated attestation role. Scope: recompute plan cost from the extracted DAG with DAG-aware memoization, reject cost mismatches explicitly, and add focused regression tests.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"LavenderFalcon","created_at":"2026-03-13T02:11:57.575065943Z","created_by":"LavenderFalcon","updated_at":"2026-03-13T06:22:29.358503092Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T06:22:29.358456836Z","close_reason":"Fixed at HEAD: ExtractionCertificate::verify now rejects tampered cost metadata; targeted regression test and cargo check passed via rch. Workspace cargo clippy remains blocked by unrelated pre-existing failures in src/net/websocket/client.rs and src/web/negotiate.rs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.307","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T02:11:57.575065943Z","created_by":"LavenderFalcon"}]}
